---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 26, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Neutralized dog-coded wording across 14 shared workflow pages so every <a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/*</a> page reads correctly for all nine supported species, and shipped a new <a href="/workflows/kidding-management" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/kidding-management</a> workflow for goat and sheep breeders to mirror the existing <a href="/workflows/foaling-management" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/foaling-management</a> page for horse breeders.</p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">New workflow page: Kidding &amp; Lambing Management</h3>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Covers caprine and ovine pregnancy with the species-appropriate 150-day (goat) and 147-day (sheep) gestation lengths.</li>
    <li>Standard milestone schedule: day 45 confirmation, day 75 fetal count, day 100 mid-gestation, day 120 CDT booster, day 135 BoSe + pre-kidding prep, day 145+ pre-kidding signs watch.</li>
    <li>Exposure-window support so does and ewes bred on a buck-in / buck-out window get a kidding window, not a single date.</li>
    <li>Pre-kidding sign checklist tuned for does and ewes: udder development, ligament softening (tail-head test), vulvar swelling, restlessness, off-feed, vocalization.</li>
    <li>Multi-kid outcome recording per dam (singles, twins, triplets, quads) with per-kid presentation, birth weight, dam-raised vs. bottle-raised vs. CAE-prevention pulled, disbudding scheduling, and tattoo recording.</li>
    <li>Registry-aware (ADGA, AGS, ABGA, USBGR, NSIP) and CAE-prevention aware (heat-treated colostrum + pasteurized milk decision tracked pre-kidding, not improvised in the moment).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Shared workflow pages neutralized</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Every page under <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/workflows/*</code> is shared across all nine supported species per the <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">breederhq-www</code> tone rule. Phase 1 covered low-hit pages, Phase 2 covered the high-hit rewrites:</p>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Low-hit cleanup (1-5 dog-coded hits per page):</strong> titles-competitions, scout-ai, medication-tracking, nutrition-tracking, embed-on-your-website, communications-hub, client-management, client-portal, marketplace, invoicing-expenses, heat-tracking, breeding-cycles, breeding-plans, breeding-intelligence. Whelping references replaced with species-aware due-date framing (whelping / foaling / kidding / lambing / kindling / calving). "Puppy buyer" references in cross-link descriptions changed to "buyers (any species)." Genetics-prediction "litter" terms moved to "offspring group" where appropriate.</li>
    <li><strong>High-hit rewrites:</strong> offspring-care (16 dog-coded hits), rearing-protocols (13), waitlists-and-placement (9), outreach-hub (12). FAQ answers, hero subheads, screenshot alt text, and Related Workflows cross-links all updated to enumerate the multi-species reality. The dog-specific protocol sections in rearing-protocols (ENS, ESI, Rule of 7s, Volhard PAT, Gun Dog Aptitude) were intentionally left as-is — they are real published protocols and the page already labels them dog-specific with a separate multi-species section beneath.</li>
    <li><strong>Cross-link wiring:</strong> Foaling Management and Kidding &amp; Lambing Management are now reciprocally linked from breeding-cycles and offspring-care. Two broken links to a non-existent <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/litter-management</code> page were removed (offspring-care CTA + waitlists-and-placement / client-portal "Learn more" sections).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Navigation and CTA wiring for the new page</h3>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Header workflows dropdown gained a "Kidding &amp; Lambing Management" entry next to "Foaling Management."</li>
    <li><a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows</a> index gained a card for Kidding &amp; Lambing Management.</li>
    <li><a href="/goats" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/goats</a> secondary CTA repointed from <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/workflows/breeding-cycles</code> (a shared page) to <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/compare/best-goat-breeding-software</code>, which is the goat-native comparison page that pairs with the new kidding workflow.</li>
    <li><a href="/goats" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/goats</a>, <a href="/sheep" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/sheep</a>, <a href="/compare/best-goat-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-goat-breeding-software</a>, <a href="/compare/best-sheep-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-sheep-breeding-software</a>, <a href="/workflows/foaling-management" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/foaling-management</a>, <a href="/workflows/breeding-cycles" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/breeding-cycles</a>, and <a href="/workflows/offspring-care" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/offspring-care</a> all gained Related Workflows cross-links to the new page so it does not become a discovery orphan.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Structural decision: keep foaling-management as horse-specific, add kidding-management as a goat/sheep peer</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">The roadmap raised the question of whether to rename <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/workflows/foaling-management</code> to <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/workflows/birthing-management</code> as a single species-neutral page. We explicitly chose the opposite: keep <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">foaling-management</code> as the horse-specific birth workflow page, and add <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">kidding-management</code> as its caprine/ovine peer.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Three reasons:</p>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Existing inbound links.</strong> Renaming <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">foaling-management</code> would create redirect debt across the Header, the <a href="/horses" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/horses</a> page, <a href="/compare/best-horse-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-horse-breeding-software</a>, <a href="/workflows/mare-reproductive-tracking" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/mare-reproductive-tracking</a>, <a href="/workflows/stallion-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/stallion-services</a>, <a href="/workflows/breeding-cycles" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/breeding-cycles</a>, and several site-updates fragments.</li>
    <li><strong>Biology differs enough to warrant separate pages.</strong> Equine pregnancy is 11 months with twin-detection as a critical day-15 milestone. Caprine/ovine pregnancy is 5 months with multiple-kid presentations as the norm rather than a complication, and CDT/BoSe/CAE-prevention as species-specific concerns that horse breeders never deal with. A single neutral page either becomes vague or becomes an unwieldy two-page page-in-one.</li>
    <li><strong>Tone discipline matches the existing pattern.</strong> The site already runs the model of "shared workflow pages neutral, species-specific landing pages and software-comparison pages dedicated." Adding a species-specific birth workflow per major species cluster (equine, caprine/ovine, future canine) is consistent with how <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/horses</code>, <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/goats</code>, <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/sheep</code>, and the species-specific compare pages already work.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Why this matters</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">The goat audit flagged that every <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/workflows/*</code> page was using whelping / litters / puppies vocabulary on what is supposed to be a multi-species shared surface, and that horse breeders had a dedicated <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/workflows/foaling-management</code> page while goat and sheep breeders had nothing equivalent. The audit treated this as an asymmetry that made the goat category read as a content island whenever a buyer clicked beyond <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/goats</code> itself. Both halves of that gap are now closed in a single ship: the shared pages are neutralized and the species-specific peer page exists.</p>
</article>
